			<div class="content" id="post-content-3781024">
									

<p>Well, there are two types of eclipses.<br />
A solar eclipse is one possibility, in which the moon temporarily passes in between the sun and the earth, blocking the light of the sun partially or totally.</p>
<p>A lunar eclipse is another variant of an eclipse in which the earth blocks the light to the moon. A lunar eclipse is sometimes referred to as a blood moon.</p>
<p>And that is what happens during an eclipse.</p>

